Description: Prolog is a logic programming language associated with artificial intelligence and computational linguistics

Program 2:Find out whether an element is a member of the list using recursion

Code:
% Base case: Element is the head of the list.
member(X, [X|_]).
% Recursive case: Element is in the tail of the list.
member(X, [_|T]) :- member(X, T).

Queries:
member(2, [1, 2, 3]).
member(4, [1, 2, 3]). 
member(john, [mary, jane, john]). 
member(pizza, [sushi, burger, pizza]).

The output of Queries: True
False
True
True
